Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 475 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Trim, peel, and slice half the @Red Onion{1}(trimmed, peeled, and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings); mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4). Quarter @Lemon{1}(quartered). Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced).

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

== Pico de Gallo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice (juice from half a lemon for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Filling ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced onion, salt, and pepper. Cook until veggies are softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. (TIP: Add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.) Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add a drizzle of oil to same pan. Add chicken and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Return veggies to pan. Stir in half the @Tex-Mex Paste{1%unit}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Cook until everything is coated and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Place a small amount of filling on one half of each @Flour Tortillas{6%unit}. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create enchiladas. Place, seam sides down, in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch dish for 4 servings) or #ovenproof pan{}.

In a second small bowl, combine @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce}, remaining Tex-Mex paste, remaining Southwest Spice, and @water{1/2%cup} (3/4 cup for 4 servings).

Pour sauce over enchiladas to thoroughly coat. Sprinkle with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}.

Bake on top rack until sauce is bubbly and cheese melts, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Top enchiladas with pico de gallo. Divide between plates. Dollop with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.